<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Browse account holders</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    Click <strong>Accounts</strong> in the left sidebar. You'll see 40 pre-seeded account holders across 2 pages.
  </li>
  <li>
    Each account shows the <strong>reference number</strong>, <strong>name</strong>, <strong>address</strong>, and <strong>current balance</strong> (in pounds sterling).
  </li>
  <li>
    Try the <strong>search filters</strong> — search by account reference, surname, fund type, postcode, or address.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click <strong>View</strong> on any account to see full details — title, name, address, fund name, period debit/credit, and creation date.
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Explore transactions</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    Click <strong>Transactions</strong> in the sidebar. You'll see 500 pre-seeded transactions across 25 pages.
  </li>
  <li>
    Transactions span multiple <strong>fund types</strong> — Council Tax, Parking Fines, Business Rates, Benefit Overpayments, and more.
  </li>
  <li>
    Each transaction shows the <strong>date</strong>, <strong>method of payment (MOP)</strong>, <strong>receipt reference</strong>, <strong>fund type</strong>, <strong>account</strong>, <strong>narrative</strong>, and <strong>amount</strong>.
  </li>
  <li>
    Use the comprehensive search filters — filter by fund type, MOP code, date range, amount, account reference, or narrative.
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <strong>Real-world context:</strong> In a live council deployment, these transactions would come from citizen payments via GOV.UK Pay, bank file imports, counter payments, and automated standing orders.
</div>
